Following a group of student vets who have been studying for four years at the Royal Veterinary College and are finally putting their textbooks to one side and getting hands-on with real animals.

1/10 Elly must anaesthetise a kitten with serious breathing problems.

2/10 Judy attempts to help a border collie with a broken back.

3/10 The intense pressure is starting to take its toll on some of the students.
 
4/10 The vets tackle some smelly jobs and learn that not all cases end happily.
 
5/10 Matt treats a dog who has had a series of seizures and cannot walk. 
 
6/10 Charlie cares for a dog who almost dies after surgery. 

7/10 Elly treats a seriously ill golden retriever with swelling and infection around his heart. 
  
8/10 Charlie treats a flat-coated retriever involved in a serious road accident. 
 
9/10 Dru treats a young labrador suffering from New Forest syndrome. 
 
10/10 The students find out whether they have succeeded in becoming fully qualified vets.
